The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 01 December is 1,413,410 (2,511.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 November, there were 91,376 new confirmed cases (162.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 November, there were 129,633 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 30% (38,257 fewer cases).
